{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fe1e294d-4bfd-4b5e-99e8-1ab62e20ae80","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Install the SDK** — Download .NET 11 SDK from https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/11.0\n\n**5. Review breaking changes** — Check the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API or behavioral changes affecting your app.\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet build && dotnet test` to verify everything compiles and passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2f34b233-0693-4de2-a508-8d2801a67a4f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":316,"requestId":"6809:CCC04:1046948:149E4FA:69FFE314"},"id":"2bc3b4ac-c16c-4293-9824-a53d99cc51da","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:44:59.616Z","parentId":"d3ca122a-9833-4753-b8d6-309edc3f1ded"}
